==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia2|hypocoristic}}
'''hypocorism'''

===Meaning===
#A form of [[endearment]]; a [[pet]] [[name]]
#The use of pet names

===Etymology===
Late Latin '''hypocorisma''', a loan from Greek noun υποκορισ ('''hypokorisma''') from the verb ('''hypokorizesthai''' = 'to call by pet names'). The Greek verb ''hypokorizesthai'' is compounded from [[υπο]] ([[hypo]]- = 'under') + κορ (korzesthai = 'to [[caress]]'). In the verb you can see the word κορος (koros = '[[boy]]') or κορη (kore = '[[girl]]').

